    "body": "builds on #40175\nrelated #40222\n\n## Problem\n\n#40175 adds attach-time terminal probing for remote UIs, but terminal responses still need an actual identity before I can even begin to work on per-UI state. A sort of prerequisite prerequisite change. This PR does not make options or colorschemes per-UI.\n\n## Solution\n\nInclude the RPC source channel in `TermResponse` event data and let `vim.tty.request()` callers filter by that channel.\n\nIf accepted, I will follow up this PR by auditing all builtin terminal probes/queries and apply channel filtering appropriately (i.e. where the request has a clear UI owner). I will make a table of accept/reject call sites so anyone can audit my decisions there too. I figured this is a big enough change on its own.\n",
    "closed_at": null,
